# SPA fallback rules for Cloudflare Pages.
#
# IMPORTANT: do NOT use broad rules like `/:org` or `/:org/*` here.
# Empirically, Cloudflare Pages applies _redirects placeholder rules
# BEFORE static file lookup (despite what the docs say), so a broad
# `/:org` would shadow root files like /og-image.png and /robots.txt,
# and `/:org/*` would shadow /astro-assets/*.js etc.
#
# Instead, list each dashboard sub-path explicitly. The second path
# segment is a fixed literal, so single-segment static files at root
# (favicon.ico, og-image.png, robots.txt) keep working.

# /app resolver
/app          /spa/  200
/app/*        /spa/  200

# Public booking + share links
/share/*      /spa/  200
/book/*       /spa/  200

# Org dashboard sub-paths (mirrors routes in client/src/router.tsx)
/:org/calendar        /spa/  200
/:org/members         /spa/  200
/:org/meeting-rooms   /spa/  200
/:org/insights        /spa/  200
/:org/revenue         /spa/  200
/:org/expenses        /spa/  200
/:org/waiting-list    /spa/  200
/:org/organization    /spa/  200
/:org/rooms           /spa/  200
/:org/plans           /spa/  200
/:org/team            /spa/  200
/:org/notifications   /spa/  200
/:org/integrations    /spa/  200
/:org/admin           /spa/  200
